HEADWORD: Masher
<hw>Mash"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, mashes; also <fld>(Brewing)</fld>, a machine for making
mash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A charmer of women.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>
<rj><au>London Punch.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mashy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Mashie</ent>⟦br⟧
